1
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,600
You really don't want to get a Ph.D.?

2
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,560
Absolutely not.

3
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,720
Then why don't you just join us at Flight Control?

4
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,880
This year, I want to organize

5
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,080
the promising newcomers

6
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:43,120
and form a

7
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,600
Muxing Team.

8
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,640
It's entirely based on young people's concepts.

9
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,039
The tasks

10
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:50,320
will be more flexible

11
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,400
and freer.

12
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,240
Don't you have internship experience?

13
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,920
Why don't you think about it?

14
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,560
Mr. Qin, please don't try to persuade me.

15
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,090
I don't want to go anywhere.

16
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,880
I don't want to persuade you.

17
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,720
I won't lead a horse to water and make it drink.

18
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,320
I wouldn't do such a thing.

19
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,780
Wouldn't that make me just like your mother?

20
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:12,120
Actually, you should be able to understand

21
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:15,160
your mother's good intentions.

22
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,200
At her age,

23
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,520
a son means everything

24
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,600
to a mother.

25
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,560
Every grade you've gotten since you were a child,

26
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,490
you can see how much weight it holds

27
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,000
in her heart, right?

28
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,280
Of course, you are a child

29
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,360
who hates being controlled.

30
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,760
You're born rebellious.

31
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,760
The more you arrange for me,

32
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:39,000
the less I want it.

33
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:40,079
Right?

34
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,720
But,

35
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,280
the current situation between you two,

36
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:49,840
living under the same roof every day,

37
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:52,210
won't it just intensify the conflict?

38
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,300
How about this?

39
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:58,210
Flight Control recently allocated a dorm building,

40
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,329
a bachelor dorm.

41
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,120
They are all brand new,

42
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,360
fully furnished.

43
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,120
I can arrange for you

44
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,850
to go there and hide for a while.

45
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:06,940
What do you say?

46
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:10,480
Of course, our side

47
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,000
is strictly managed.

48
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,400
It's a closed management system,

49
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,600
you can't just come and go as you please.

50
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,440
I don't know if you can stand it.

51
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,800
Think about it.

52
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,320
If you come,

53
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:27,240
I'll go talk to your mom.

54
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,800
I've also communicated with Mr. Qiao.

55
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,530
He will talk to your mother too.

56
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:35,960
Mr. Qin,

57
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,260
thank you for the invitation,

58
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,260
but I really have no such plans right now.

59
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:49,040
You have your plans,

60
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,760
and I have my own rules.

61
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,840
I like your personality.

62
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,040
Weiwei,

63
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,320
why did you just get back?

64
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:10,450
How was the Flight Control interview?

65
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,760
Come, do me a favor.

66
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,000
Press this here.

67
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,160
Don't move.

68
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,920
Seeing you so listless,

69
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:26,650
did you fail?

70
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:28,810
That's fine.

71
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,400
If this path doesn't work out,

72
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,760
let's not force it.

73
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,400
Doesn't your major have many career paths?

74
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,240
Hurry up and find a company to work for.

75
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,760
Didn't many companies give you those,

76
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,960
what do you call them,

77
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:39,920
offer letters?

78
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:42,320
Pick one carefully.

79
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,920
I plan

80
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:49,610
to try the Space City Archives.

81
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,120
With your major,

82
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,850
what can you do at the archives?

83
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,730
Probably an archives administrator.

84
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,920
Let me tell you,

85
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,360
your father is a cautionary tale for you,

86
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,490
a negative example.

87
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,600
Back in the day, at least

88
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,920
I was a communications equipment technician.

89
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,800
I was spoiled for choice and got confused.

90
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,720
Out of so many companies,

91
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,880
I just had to pick a pager company.

92
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,400
My youth and the first half of my life

93
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,400
were all wasted there.

94
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,200
Did someone cast a spell on you?

95
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,600
You insist on being an administrator at Space City.

96
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,160
No way.

97
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,080
I'm going anyway.

98
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,080
Even if it's just an administrator,

99
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:22,600
it's an administrator at Space City.

100
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,360
What do you know?

101
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,560
This is called finding a new path.

102
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,760
I rejected all those job offers.

103
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:26,600
Enough, stay out of this.

104
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,240
I can decide for myself.

105
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:27,680
You...

106
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,080
Stop right there!

107
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,680
You rejected them all?

108
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,600
So many people fight tooth and nail

109
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,640
just to get in but can't,

110
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,720
and you rejected them?

111
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,040
On what grounds did you reject them?

112
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,770
Do you have the final say or do I?

113
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,320
Go find a company and work properly.

114
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,080
I won't listen to you.

115
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,720
If you don't let me go, my mom will.

116
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,850
Your son is going to work in aerospace!

117
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,400
I am your father!

118
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:48,960
I...

119
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,880
What's going on? Is everything okay?

120
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,800
It's nothing.

121
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,880
Fine, let's eat.

122
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:06,210
Let's eat first. We'll talk after dinner.

123
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,600
Weiwei.

124
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:48,960
You truly live up to taking your mother's surname.

125
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,520
Every move you make is just like her.

126
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:55,000
Back then, when your mom wanted to do logistics in aerospace,

127
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,130
your grandma was strongly against it.

128
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,440
She said,

129
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:01,000
'Our daughter is a proper

130
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:03,530
college student majoring in statistics,

131
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,000
what is she going to do at Space City?

132
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,520
What can she achieve by doing logistics?'

133
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,640
I remember because of this,

134
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:13,040
your mom and your grandma argued

135
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,080
so fiercely.

136
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,680
To be honest, if I wasn't in the middle

137
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,080
mediating between them,

138
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,420
I'm telling you, they would have fought.

139
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,720
I was just a geography teacher,

140
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,200
if my daughter could work in aerospace,

141
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,180
what else was there to say?

142
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,520
Go for it.

143
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,960
At the time, I just felt that

144
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:33,480
they always worked overtime there,

145
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,640
and I was worried

146
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,300
it would exhaust my daughter.

147
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,360
Ultimately,

148
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,800
children grow up.

149
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:48,159
The path they take is the one they choose.

150
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:50,159
The life they live

151
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,960
is the life they choose.

152
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:55,480
As fathers and mothers,

153
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,540
no matter how much you love your kids,

154
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,159
you can't live

155
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,530
their whole lives for them.

156
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:02,520
Right?

157
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,010
What should a father do?

158
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:13,130
A father must be able to shoulder responsibilities.

159
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:15,000
You... tell your dad...

160
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,250
Ever since he came to our Wu family,

161
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:21,440
your mom has been so busy working in aerospace.

162
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,600
He manages everything inside and outside the house,

163
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,080
taking care of you

164
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,600
and raising you with all his might,

165
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,130
bringing you up to this age.

166
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,520
Is it easy for him?

167
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,240
He also takes care of us old folks.

168
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,880
It's so hard for him.

169
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,240
Whether we work in the archives

170
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,120
or flight control,

171
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:44,600
as long as it's in aerospace, it's fine.

172
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:48,200
Just go report to the archives properly.

173
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,160
Weiwei.

174
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:39,520
Weiwei.

175
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,720
Mom.

176
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,960
How did you get so dirty?

177
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,880
Sit down.

178
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,740
Let mom wipe it for you.

179
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,760
Are you a little dirty cat?

180
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,600
Look at your helmet.

181
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,400
Let's wipe it.

182
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:14,840
Mom.

183
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,360
I miss you.

184
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:20,560
Weiwei,

185
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,480
did something happen?

186
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,640
Tell mom.

187
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,120
Nothing much.

188
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:32,280
It's just that I encountered many things

189
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,680
and always get rejected.

190
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,960
I don't know

191
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,090
if there's any point in holding on.

192
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,690
How could there be no point?

193
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,650
Holding on is the point.

194
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:45,400
Weiwei,

195
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,960
others may reject you,

196
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,440
but what about yourself?

197
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,480
Don't be afraid.

198
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,140
No matter what others say,

199
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:00,010
Mom will always believe in you.

200
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:11,680
It's clean now.

201
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:29,680
Mom,

202
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:31,840
let's go home.

203
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:41,080
Shall we go eat?

204
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,620
Mom will make you sweet and sour ribs.

205
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:44,320
Okay.

206
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:48,160
Today at 19:41,

207
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:50,280
the Zhengtu-7 Yao-2 carrier rocket,

208
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,600
carrying the Longzhou-1 cargo spacecraft,

209
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:55,800
was ignited and launched at the Wenchang Space Launch Site in China.

210
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,160
About 596 seconds later,

211
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,200
the spacecraft successfully separated from the rocket

212
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,520
and entered the designated orbit.

213
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,280
The launch was a complete success.

214
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:02,800
Next,

215
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,680
let's invite Chief Designer Chu Jiajia

216
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,400
to give a brief introduction.

217
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,480
Next,

218
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,240
Longzhou-1 will pass through the 400-meter

219
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,970
and 120-meter parking points,

220
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:15,840
and finally complete

221
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,370
the rendezvous and docking with Longgong-2.

222
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,640
Xiaoqi.

223
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,520
Come, get up.

224
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,160
Be good.

225
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,120
Son,

226
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,360
let dad tell you some news.

227
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,800
You must not sell me out.

228
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:57,080
Mr. Qin from the other day

229
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,760
has already promised your mom

230
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,690
to help you find a reliable mentor.

231
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,040
Ying Ziqi.

232
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,320
Yesterday, your mom

233
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,000
put away your IDs.

234
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:12,360
Tell me,

235
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:13,920
if you lack these,

236
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,200
how can you go out

237
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,160
and get a job?

238
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,600
So for now,

239
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,440
just eat and drink as usual.

240
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:21,520
Let's just wait and see.

241
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:23,740
What are you doing?

242
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,560
No, be gentle.

243
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,320
If your mom hears us,

244
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,400
we're both dead.

245
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,570
What are you going to do?

246
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,520
Let's talk this out.

247
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,690
Where are you going?

248
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:41,680
Xiaoqi.

249
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:42,720
Xiaoqi.

250
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:43,840
Xiaoqi.

251
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,450
You're slipping away, aren't you?

252
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,160
Don't be so disloyal.

253
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,940
Aren't you selling me out?

254
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Think about it.

255
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:03,000
I've lived with your mom for over 20 years.

256
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,040
If I fall out with her

257
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,370
over your little issue,

258
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,800
is it worth it?

259
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:10,000
Besides, your mom treats you like this

260
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,360
for a reason.

261
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,240
You should understand her.

262
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:14,120
Dad,

263
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:16,320
I've thought about it for a long time.

264
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,580
I haven't figured out what I really want.

265
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:19,880
Don't get worked up.

266
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:20,560
Keep your voice down.

267
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,560
But I know exactly what I don't want.

268
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,560
I don't want this kind of life.

269
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,080
I don't want this kind of family.

270
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,610
And I definitely don't want

271
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,520
a mom like this.

272
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:30,560
Ziqi.

273
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,540
What are you doing?

274
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,640
If your mom hears this,

275
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,920
she'll be so sad.

276
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:39,520
What are you doing?

277
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,840
Are you really leaving?

278
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,040
You're too disloyal.

279
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:49,560
Hello, Mr. Qin.

280
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:51,520
I'm Ying Ziqi.

281
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,840
You mentioned before,

282
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,400
is the quota for flight control still open?

283
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,240
It is.

284
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:57,170
We've been waiting for you.

285
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,140
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

286
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:43,360
Hello.

287
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,400
Go forward, it's here.

288
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,640
Hello, sir.

289
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,200
Are you new?

290
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:53,760
If you need to look up materials, go over there,

291
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,490
and swipe your badge yourself.

292
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:56,360
No, sir.

293
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,400
I'm here for the archives.

294
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,930
I'm here to report for duty.

295
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,000
Archivist?

296
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,600
Are you Wu Wei?

297
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:19,920
Navigation, Guidance and Control.

298
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:26,360
Why didn't you interview at the Flight Control Center?

299
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,360
I...

300
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,800
I was originally going to Flight Control.

301
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,200
But I got rejected.

302
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,200
I heard from Mr. Qin Bojun

303
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,680
that the archives are hiring.

304
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,140
So I wanted to give it a try.

305
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,360
It's a way to fulfill my space dream.

306
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,400
I've wanted to be an astronaut since I was a kid.

307
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,760
But because my eyesight is poor,

308
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:45,120
I was rejected for that too.

309
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,400
But I've figured it out.

310
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,440
I just need to adapt.

311
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,600
As long as I can work in the space industry,

312
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:49,930
I'll take any position.

313
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:52,280
OK.

314
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,320
You are still a kid with a dream.

315
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:55,760
Not bad.

316
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:56,800
I like it.

317
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,920
If not an astronaut, then flight control.

318
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:02,250
If not flight control, then the archives.

319
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:06,920
What do you take my archives for?

320
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,839
A stepping stone or an asylum?

321
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:12,400
No, no, sir.

322
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,160
Sir.

323
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:13,800
I...

324
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,839
I didn't take the archives as a stepping stone,

325
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:17,680
nor an asylum.

326
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,440
I don't think an archivist

327
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,359
is a bad job.

328
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:21,640
Rest assured, since I'm here,

329
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,800
I will work hard.

330
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,599
All right, fine.

331
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,000
You can go.

332
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Please, sir.

333
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:31,970
Give me one more chance.

334
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,800
Didn't I give you a chance?

335
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,160
You did?

336
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,520
This is...

337
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,600
I'm assigning you a vehicle.

338
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,760
Let me tell you,

339
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:46,040
it's for official use only.

340
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,320
I get a vehicle?

341
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:49,240
Of course.

342
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,680
This is our archives'

343
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,840
ancestral BMW.

344
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,650
What are you looking at?

345
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:10,000
I saw one over there.

346
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,080
I was thinking,

347
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:13,720
the treasure of our archives

348
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:16,280
should at least be a rocket model.

349
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,680
So...

350
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,240
See the pen?

351
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,720
Do you know what kind of pen it is?

352
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,060
A fountain pen.

353
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:29,080
Very smart.

354
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:30,320
Isn't that obvious?

355
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,040
Yes.

356
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:33,960
Do you know why I put it there?

357
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,940
Because it's very memorable.

358
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,770
Do you know who gave it to me?

359
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:40,890
I don't know.

360
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:42,540
Let me tell you,

361
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:46,300
you are not qualified to know yet.

362
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,240
Go, report to your dorm.

363
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:49,840
Off you go.

364
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:52,320
I'll come to work tomorrow then.

365
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,360
Goodbye, sir.

366
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,220
Okay, goodbye.

367
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:12,920
A BMW, huh?

368
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,440
What a treasure.

369
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:49,600
Dad.

370
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,120
I am in Aerospace City now,

371
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,780
in the newly built staff dorm.

372
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:53,940
It's a double room,

373
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:56,280
but Mr. Qin specially approved it for me alone.

374
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,240
Starting today,

375
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:59,480
I will live a life of muddling along.

376
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:00,680
Dad,

377
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,520
don't worry.

378
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,680
Take good care of yourself then.

379
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,520
I will talk to your mom.

380
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,360
Reporting to you, sir.

381
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,360
Newcomer Wu Wei reporting for duty.

382
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,200
Wu Wei?

383
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,160
You?

384
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:20,040
Why are you here?

385
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,000
What are you doing in my dorm?

386
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,320
What are you doing in my dorm?

387
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:23,520
You are staying here?

388
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:28,760
You...

389
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,060
Hello, Mr. Qin?

390
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:41,520
It's me.

391
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:45,920
Didn't we agree on a single dorm?

392
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:48,050
Why is there an extra person in my room?

393
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:50,080
What person?

394
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,730
There's an extra person living in my room.

395
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:57,890
It's a singles dorm.

396
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,720
He's also single.

397
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,730
You two share it.

398
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,290
The kind of single room you mentioned does exist,

399
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,760
but it's usually reserved for working couples,

400
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:10,090
and the environment isn't as good as here.

401
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,400
Wait until one opens up.

402
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,660
I'll take you to see it.

403
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,960
Just bear with it for now.

404
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:16,240
I can't bear it for another second.

405
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:16,800
Mr. Qin.

406
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:17,920
You promised me.

407
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:20,250
Please help me solve this quickly.

408
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,000
If you have a problem, say it to my face.

409
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,560
Why tattle behind my back?

410
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,260
I'm tattling to your face.

411
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:37,480
That was Aunt Chen on the day of the robotics competition, right?

412
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,880
She hasn't changed a bit.

413
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:39,960
Does she still

414
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,960
control you like when you were a kid?

415
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,640
None of your business.

416
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:44,440
Look at you.

417
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:47,200
You stole the championship,

418
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,560
and I didn't say anything.

419
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:50,040
We haven't seen each other for so many years.

420
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,240
Let's catch up.

421
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,740
It's better not to see each other.

422
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,120
Remember,

423
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,730
counting the rocket competition,

424
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:58,680
you owe me two.

425
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,460
Nobody owes you anything.

426
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,120
Take your stuff and leave.

427
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:03,040
What if I don't?

428
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:06,210
If you have a problem, move out.

429
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,760
Make some room for me.

430
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:10,250
As if anyone wants to live with you.

431
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:11,800
If anyone's moving, it's you.

432
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:12,680
Don't you understand first come, first served?

433
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,640
Whoever complains more moves out.

434
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:16,560
Aerospace City is all about ability.

435
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:17,160
Ability?

436
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:18,420
Do you have any?

437
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,420
Let's compete.

438
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,440
Are you an elementary schooler?

439
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,920
Then bring on a college-level one.

440
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,250
Come on, let me show you.

441
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,720
Fibonacci sequence.

442
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,640
Even elementary schoolers know it.

443
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,480
So what?

444
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,360
Based on the first set of solutions I gave,

445
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:25,560
find the second set.

446
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,600
Calculate it.

447
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,820
I'm timing you.

448
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,760
If you don't even understand the question,

449
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:56,440
don't talk about ability.

450
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,200
Who claimed

451
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:18,000
to be a Math Olympiad top student since childhood?

452
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:19,800
Me?

453
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,320
Apparently not.

454
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:29,640
Wait.

455
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:34,960
This question of yours has absolutely no mathematical correlation.

456
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:35,840
Stop bluffing.

457
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:37,800
Is it possible

458
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:40,120
that it's a geometric correlation?

459
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:43,960
Zero circles.

460
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,320
One, two, three.

461
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:46,200
Three circles.

462
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,520
Two, three, four.

463
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:48,360
Four circles.

464
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:50,320
One circle. One circle.

465
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:55,780
A kindergarten entrance exam question.

466
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,410
Understood? Applause.

467
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,720
Not convinced?

468
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,120
Give me one if you're not.

469
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:06,250
A leopard cannot change its spots.

470
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,600
One monkey riding on a tree, one monkey on the ground.

471
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,600
How many monkeys are there in total?

472
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,440
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

473
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,300
No problem,

474
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,440
sorry about that.

475
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,080
Sorry.

476
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,760
Three-second rule. It's still good to eat.

477
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,800
I'm sorry.

478
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,490
Still good, no worries.

479
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,120
Ying.

480
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:43,040
I heard

481
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,300
you were specially recruited by Mr. Qin.

482
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,440
Nice to meet you.

483
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:48,640
You are indeed different.

484
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,840
Nice jacket and shoes.

485
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:52,680
Let me introduce myself.

486
00:25:52,680 --> 00:25:53,640
I'm Cai Bo'ao.

487
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,900
You can call me Caibao.

488
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:56,920
Hello.

489
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,640
This is Qu Ruonan.

490
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,480
A top student from the University of Technology.

491
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:01,880
We attended an interview together before.

492
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,120
Qu Ruonan, nice to meet you.

493
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:07,840
Are you okay just now?

494
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,300
I'm fine, perfectly fine.

495
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:10,080
Let's go.

496
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,160
Registration is about to start.

497
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:11,880
Hurry up.

498
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,300
I also love chocolate.

499
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:27,040
Morning, Mr. Zhao.

500
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,100
I'm here to report.

501
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,170
You're here.

502
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,120
By the way, Wu Wei,

503
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,880
do you play chess?

504
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:35,560
No.

505
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:40,520
Get to work.

506
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,000
Mr. Zhao,

507
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,640
what should I do today?

508
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:52,980
What should I be busy with?

509
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:57,520
That pile of trash on the desk,

510
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,980
throw it away for me first.

511
00:27:01,080 --> 00:27:02,140
That pile of paper?

512
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:03,570
Yes, that pile of paper.

513
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:21,320
Pick them out.

514
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,840
I told you to throw it away and you just did it?

515
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:31,640
You didn't even check if there's

516
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,720
any important data in this pile of trash.

517
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:36,520
Our archives are full of classified information.

518
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:38,160
What if there is

519
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,220
important data in this pile of trash?

520
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,200
Have you read the work manual?

521
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:50,160
Have you memorized the confidentiality rules?

522
00:27:50,160 --> 00:27:51,890
Did you hear me? I'm asking you.

523
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:55,240
Mr. Zhao, it's my first day of work today.

524
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,160
So?

525
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,680
Is the first day of work an excuse?

526
00:27:58,680 --> 00:27:59,320
Is it?

527
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:03,000
When was the work manual given to you?

528
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:03,760
Yesterday.

529
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:04,720
What did you do?

530
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:10,360
Mr. Zhao, I will definitely read it carefully.

531
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,640
If you have any requirements in the future,

532
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,370
you can tell me directly first.

533
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,960
Are you still unconvinced, kid?

534
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,040
Do you think I'm setting you up?

535
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,200
Yes.

536
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:23,080
I just want to test you.

537
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:26,210
If you really have confidence, would you be exposed?

538
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:31,400
Wu Wei.

539
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:34,320
The rules in Space City are rules.

540
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,200
This must be carved into your bones.

541
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:39,680
I shouldn't need to remind you again.

542
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,880
If you leak secrets, you will be caught.

543
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:44,210
If caught, you will be strictly punished.

544
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,000
Understood, Mr. Zhao.

545
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,360
Did you bring your work manual?

546
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:47,920
Yes,

547
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:49,240
in my bag.

548
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,480
Today, your job

549
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,840
is to carefully read the work manual.

550
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:55,160
After you finish reading,

551
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,240
help me move some things.

552
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,640
I hope you can understand.

553
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:06,440
This uniform represents honor,

554
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:07,840
responsibility,

555
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:09,480
expectation,

556
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:10,800
and duty.

557
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,400
The weight of this uniform

558
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:15,860
is far beyond what you can imagine right now.

559
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:18,360
From the moment you put on this uniform,

560
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,600
your destiny

561
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:22,080
is closely connected with every satellite.

562
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:27,800
Watching over them will be your lifelong mission.

563
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,520
This way.

564
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:37,480
All the work in our center

565
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:38,800
revolves around this big screen.

566
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:40,130
And is carried out here.

567
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,000
The upcoming Dragon Boat mission,

568
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:44,280
Ark return mission, Wentian mission,

569
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:45,840
and Haoyue mission.

570
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:49,120
All the work will be completed here.

571
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,640
Joint tests and rehearsals

572
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,970
will also be displayed on this big screen.

573
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:55,200
Our job

574
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:57,520
is to ensure that this aerospace nerve center

575
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:59,920
can operate accurately and methodically.

576
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,800
In recent years, our country's space missions

